16:58.300 --> 17:00.850
so we put it aside for the time being.
My stomach was like, groooar!
Like that!

17:00.850 --> 17:06.010
And this time, following him,
two Hashiras have had this awakening.

17:07.440 --> 17:11.720
Please teach us how to manifest it,
Kanroji and Tokito.

17:14.470 --> 17:16.070
Oh! Sure!

17:16.070 --> 17:18.150
Lady Amane is so admirable.

17:21.370 --> 17:25.160
Uh, well, so, at that time was...

17:25.160 --> 17:30.170
If I remember,
my body became very light.

17:31.420 --> 17:38.550
Um... Um... And then... It was...

17:41.050 --> 17:43.800
It was like, gwaaah!

17:43.800 --> 17:47.390
And whooom! Then, gaaah!

17:47.390 --> 17:50.140
My heart was ba-dump ba-dump nonstop!

17:50.140 --> 17:52.650
My ears rang so loud!

17:52.650 --> 17:55.270
Crack-crack-crack, like that!

18:06.950 --> 18:09.000
My deepest apologies.

18:09.000 --> 18:11.710
I would get into a hole if there was one.

18:12.960 --> 18:14.340
(Share the same brain cell with Tanjiro)

18:16.420 --> 18:18.340
Okay, it's my turn.

18:20.510 --> 18:24.140
I wasn't aware of any mark
was manifested on me.

18:24.140 --> 18:27.520
But when I think back to that battle,

18:27.520 --> 18:33.150
there are a few unusual things
that come to mind.

18:33.150 --> 18:38.320
If the conditions are met, probably
everyone could manifest the mark.

18:39.360 --> 18:42.570
Now I'm going to tell you
how I've done it.

18:54.420 --> 18:59.960
In that battle, I was poisoned
and couldn't move.

18:59.960 --> 19:02.590
When I tried to slow down
my blood circulation

19:02.590 --> 19:06.140
and the spread of the poison by
using the breathing technique,

19:06.600 --> 19:09.890
I saw the boy who wanted to
save me was nearly killed,

19:10.470 --> 19:12.560
my lost memories returned,

19:13.020 --> 19:17.940
and then I couldn't control my emotions
because I was so angry.

19:17.940 --> 19:22.820
I think my heart rate was
over two hundred per minute.

19:24.450 --> 19:27.580
Even more, my body was burning hot.

19:27.580 --> 19:32.580
My temperature must have reached
over thirty-nine degrees Celsius.

19:33.370 --> 19:37.750
How could you move in such a state?
It could be life-threatening.

19:37.750 --> 19:39.630
You're right.

19:39.630 --> 19:44.010
That's why, it was like being sifted.

19:44.630 --> 19:49.430
I think the difference between those who
manifest the mark and those who don't

19:49.430 --> 19:52.140
is whether you die or not.

19:55.520 --> 19:58.860
A heart rate over
two hundred per minute...

19:58.860 --> 20:02.900
How can you be sure your temperature
was thirty-nine degrees?

20:02.900 --> 20:09.870
Well, I had a fever when
I was being treated at Kocho's place.

20:09.870 --> 20:14.790
The thermometer showed my body
temperature was thirty-nine degrees.

20:14.790 --> 20:19.790
I felt it was the same heat
when the mark manifested.

20:22.340 --> 20:23.760
I didn't realize.

20:25.300 --> 20:28.340
So, it's really that simple.

20:28.340 --> 20:33.350
I envy you for being a simpleton
to call that is simple.

20:34.020 --> 20:35.980
What did you say?

20:35.980 --> 20:37.140
Nothing.

20:40.940 --> 20:45.280
That means we Hashiras
must manifest the mark.

20:45.860 --> 20:47.070
Agreed.

20:47.070 --> 20:49.570
We will do something about it.

20:49.570 --> 20:54.410
Please tell the Master to rest assured.

20:54.410 --> 20:56.620
Thank you.

20:56.620 --> 21:00.170
There is one thing I must tell you

21:00.170 --> 21:03.710
regarding the training to
manifest the mark.

21:03.710 --> 21:05.920
What is it?

21:06.340 --> 21:11.930
Those who have manifested the mark
will have no choice anymore.

21:12.680 --> 21:17.810
Because they, without exception, will—

21:38.960 --> 21:40.170
I understand now.

21:40.670 --> 21:44.710
But in that case,
what would happen to me?

21:44.710 --> 21:46.420
Good Lord.

21:46.760 --> 21:50.180
Since Lady Amane has left,
I have nothing to do here.

21:50.180 --> 21:53.470
Hey, hold on! Don't just leave!

21:53.470 --> 21:58.060
We have to decide what
each of us going to do.

21:58.430 --> 22:00.690
The six of you can talk yourselves.

22:00.690 --> 22:02.730
It has nothing to do with me.

22:02.730 --> 22:05.820
What do you mean by that?

22:05.820 --> 22:09.280
You're not aware enough
that you're a Hashira.

22:09.280 --> 22:14.450
Or what? So you can start
your training as soon as possible?

22:14.450 --> 22:16.870
You want to skip the meeting?

22:20.540 --> 22:22.630
Wait, you bastard!

22:22.630 --> 22:26.500
Explain yourself, Tomioka.

22:26.500 --> 22:29.380
You didn't explain enough.

22:32.380 --> 22:34.760
I'm different from you all.

22:35.390 --> 22:37.520
I don't like it.

22:37.520 --> 22:40.980
You said the same thing before,
Tomioka.

22:40.980 --> 22:43.650
Are you looking down on us?

22:43.650 --> 22:47.400
Please, don't fight! Stay calm, okay?

22:49.570 --> 22:51.070
Come back here!

22:52.110 --> 22:55.620
Ah! No, no! Please, don't!

23:02.370 --> 23:03.830
Sit down.

23:05.250 --> 23:07.460
Let's continue our discussion.

23:07.460 --> 23:09.710
I have a proposal.

23:11.510 --> 23:12.590
Here ya go.

23:12.590 --> 23:15.590
Wow! Thank you very much!

23:15.970 --> 23:18.470
You really eat a lot.

23:19.060 --> 23:22.480
Anyway, where are those three girls
and your sister?

23:22.480 --> 23:24.560
I don't see Aoi either.

23:24.560 --> 23:30.440
There's no member in critical condition,
so they've been playing with Nezuko.

23:30.440 --> 23:33.860
Thanks to them,
she's learning to speak bit by bit.

23:33.860 --> 23:36.160
Oh, I see.

23:36.160 --> 23:38.200
How peaceful.

23:38.200 --> 23:40.410
These dangos are delicious.

23:40.410 --> 23:42.790
Yeah, yeah, I know.

23:42.790 --> 23:48.040
But wouldn't it be a problem
if that Yellow-Head showed up?

23:54.800 --> 23:59.350
Oh, Zenitsu.
Are you done with your mission?

23:59.350 --> 24:01.470
I'm back, Kiyo.

24:01.470 --> 24:06.060
Everyone, Zenitsu is back!

24:09.860 --> 24:13.030
Good work on completing
your mission, Zenitsu.

24:13.030 --> 24:14.900
Good work!

24:14.900 --> 24:20.200
Kiyo, Naho, and Sumi.
You three gathered to welcome me?

24:20.870 --> 24:22.700
This time was really tough too.

24:22.700 --> 24:25.750
I thought, "I was gonna die!"
over and over.

24:25.750 --> 24:30.920
But everyone would be sad if I died,
so I did my best!

24:30.920 --> 24:33.420
I knew it, you'd be lonely
without me, right?

24:33.420 --> 24:34.920
No, we wouldn't.

24:34.920 --> 24:36.220
What?!

24:36.550 --> 24:40.220
But I'm glad you made it back alive.

24:40.680 --> 24:42.260
Uh, thanks.

24:46.640 --> 24:50.060
Oh, Zenitsu. You have returned.

24:50.060 --> 24:51.980
Good work.

24:51.980 --> 24:53.570
Aoi!

24:53.570 --> 24:58.530
Aoi, you must have missed me.
Right? I bet you've been lonely.

24:58.910 --> 25:01.450
Not really.

25:10.920 --> 25:12.880
Wel... Welcome back.

25:18.800 --> 25:20.140
So loud!

25:20.590 --> 25:22.350
Wel... Welcome back.

25:22.350 --> 25:24.350
She's so cute I could die!

25:24.350 --> 25:25.850
Sure, feel free to die!

25:26.850 --> 25:29.440
What happened, Nezuko?
You're talking!

25:29.440 --> 25:32.270
For me? Must be for me, right?
You did great just for me.

25:32.270 --> 25:34.570
I'm very happy!

25:34.570 --> 25:36.030
Please go somewhere else!

25:36.030 --> 25:39.110
Finally, we can get married!

25:39.110 --> 25:40.860
Get away from her!

25:40.860 --> 25:43.370
You looked so lovely
under the moonlight,

25:43.370 --> 25:45.620
but you're also irresistible
in the sunlight!

25:45.620 --> 25:46.790
You're wonderful!

25:46.790 --> 25:49.620
If you marry me, I'll feed you
sushi and eel every day!

25:49.620 --> 25:52.630
You can rest assured
and let's make a family!

25:53.170 --> 25:55.750
Welcome back, Inosuke.

25:59.630 --> 26:02.220
I... nosuke?

26:02.220 --> 26:05.350
Inosuke, welcome back.

26:06.970 --> 26:10.560
Where is he?
I'm gonna go and kill him.

26:10.560 --> 26:12.900
Don't say violent things!

26:12.900 --> 26:15.900
And where that Boar-Head?

26:15.900 --> 26:17.570
If you're looking for Inosuke...

26:17.570 --> 26:20.320
Huh? He was there this morning?

26:20.320 --> 26:24.950
Your sister was being taught nonstop
by that Boar-Head, you know?

26:24.950 --> 26:26.410
Being taught what?

26:26.410 --> 26:27.910
Well, about that...

26:27.910 --> 26:30.910
Inosuke! Inosuke! Inosuke! Inosuke!

26:30.910 --> 26:33.040
Imosuke. Imofuke.

26:33.040 --> 26:34.250
Boss Inosuke!

26:34.250 --> 26:35.750
Bush Imosuke.

26:35.750 --> 26:38.300
Inosuke! Inosuke! Inosuke! Inosuke!

26:38.300 --> 26:41.590
He had been trying to get her
to remember his name.

26:41.590 --> 26:44.510
Oh, I didn't know that happened.

26:44.510 --> 26:47.970
By the way, do you have
any more of these dangos?

26:47.970 --> 26:49.810
You still want more?!

27:00.150 --> 27:02.110
Haganezuka!

27:03.110 --> 27:05.120
Are your injuries okay now?

27:06.240 --> 27:07.490
I'm glad.

27:12.960 --> 27:15.290
You don't look okay!

27:17.170 --> 27:21.170
Oh, my sword. Thank you.

27:23.380 --> 27:25.640
It's Rengoku's sword guard!

27:26.760 --> 27:30.850
Thank you for protecting Kotetsu.

27:31.770 --> 27:33.890
Please have a seat.

27:33.890 --> 27:35.270
Are you all right?

27:40.900 --> 27:42.990
Blah... Bl... Bla...

27:42.990 --> 27:46.160
Do you mean the blade?
Okay, I'll look at it.

27:56.830 --> 27:58.000
Amazing.

27:58.000 --> 28:00.630
The depth of the black color
is different.

28:01.260 --> 28:03.420
The steel is of good quality.

28:03.420 --> 28:07.390
Its previous owner must have been
a very strong swordsman.

28:09.010 --> 28:10.640
The "slay" letter?

28:11.810 --> 28:17.770
The swordsmith who forged it had one goal,
it's a sword to slay all demons.

28:17.770 --> 28:23.490
He didn't engrave his name or anything
but just a single letter.

28:23.490 --> 28:27.200
The ranking system began
after this sword was made,

28:27.200 --> 28:32.160
and only the Hashiras' swords were
engraved with "Slay the Devils".

28:32.160 --> 28:35.250
Is that so?
What an incredible sword.

28:35.250 --> 28:40.540
But wait, I think there wasn't any letter
when I used this in the last battle.

28:42.300 --> 28:46.720
That's because I had only
sharpened it up to the first stage.

28:46.720 --> 28:49.850
And you guys took it from me.

28:49.850 --> 28:52.890
I hadn't cleaned the rust off.

28:52.890 --> 28:54.390
Do you want me to kill you?

28:54.390 --> 28:55.600
I'm sorry!

28:55.600 --> 29:00.020
Even now! I'm still crying because
the pain of my wounds hasn't gone!

29:00.020 --> 29:02.190
It's so hurt it's unbearable!

29:02.190 --> 29:04.610
Thanks to the interruption
while I was sharpening it!

29:04.610 --> 29:07.570
I had to start sharpening all over again!

29:08.990 --> 29:12.410
If we're talking about wounds,
his wounds were more serious.

29:12.410 --> 29:15.370
The bones all through his body
are broken.

29:19.880 --> 29:21.750
I'll kill you!

29:21.750 --> 29:23.210
You didn't hear me?

29:23.210 --> 29:24.880
Listen, Tanjiro!

29:24.880 --> 29:28.550
You will bring me mitarashi dango
until you die!

29:28.550 --> 29:30.840
You understand?! Got it?!

29:30.840 --> 29:33.220
Yes, I will.

29:33.600 --> 29:36.730
Thank you very much and get well soon.

29:37.520 --> 29:40.810
I've heard rumors about him,
but he's truly something.

29:42.150 --> 29:44.940
Actually, he was calmer than usual.

29:44.940 --> 29:46.820
He must really be in pain.

29:46.820 --> 29:48.150
Seriously?

29:48.150 --> 29:50.320
Can you be quieter, man?

29:50.320 --> 29:53.030
Oh, sorry, Genya.

29:53.030 --> 29:54.740
We're done.

29:54.740 --> 29:56.200
Sorry for being so loud—

30:05.380 --> 30:08.970
Inosuke! What are you doing?!
You broke the window!

30:10.130 --> 30:13.550
You fool!
You're gonna get killed by Lady Kocho!

30:15.310 --> 30:16.430
Be quiet!

30:16.430 --> 30:18.480
Boar Rush!

30:19.640 --> 30:22.440
I want a separate room.

30:22.440 --> 30:24.730
Strength! Strength! More strength!

30:24.730 --> 30:27.780
The joint strengthening drill
is about to begin!

30:28.110 --> 30:29.780
Joint strengthening?

30:30.110 --> 30:33.200
The strong guys are gathering
and giving lessons...

30:33.200 --> 30:35.370
Or something like that.

30:35.370 --> 30:37.410
Huh? What's that about?

30:37.410 --> 30:39.330
Dunno!

30:39.330 --> 30:40.830
I see.

30:45.040 --> 30:52.430
I think we've pretty much worked out
our training plan for the Corps members.

30:52.430 --> 30:56.350
Now left are the date and how long.

30:56.350 --> 30:58.930
Let's start in three days.

30:58.930 --> 31:01.640
Can we do it that early?

31:01.640 --> 31:04.440
We're racing against time.

31:04.440 --> 31:09.530
Now that we don't know what
Muzan Kibutsuji will do in the future,

31:09.530 --> 31:12.950
I want us to prepare everything we can.

31:12.950 --> 31:17.080
If the demons become
more active hereafter,

31:17.080 --> 31:21.000
we alone won't be
able to handle them.

31:21.000 --> 31:26.130
But, wouldn't the demons attack
while we're holding the training?

31:26.630 --> 31:32.550
It's assumed that the demons will
focus on capturing Nezuko Kamado.

31:32.550 --> 31:36.050
In fact, since the incident
in the Swordsmith Village,

31:36.050 --> 31:39.470
the appearance of the demons
has decreased significantly.

31:39.470 --> 31:41.060
If that is the case...

31:41.480 --> 31:47.520
Until now, we can hardly train others
than our Tsuguko due to our schedules.

31:47.520 --> 31:49.480
In this short period of time,

31:49.480 --> 31:54.320
We shall use this opportunity
to strengthen the entire Corps.

31:54.990 --> 31:58.080
This is important and urgent.

31:58.080 --> 32:05.580
Yes, it's important,
thus I proposed the "Hashira Training".

32:06.210 --> 32:11.210
Himejima, no need to be wordy.

32:11.210 --> 32:13.470
I concur.

32:13.470 --> 32:15.680
No objection.

32:16.760 --> 32:18.350
Me too.

32:18.350 --> 32:20.680
I also agree.

32:21.310 --> 32:26.020
Are the active Hashiras now
enough to hold the training?

32:26.020 --> 32:30.480
I'm thinking of asking
the retired Hashiras to help us.

32:30.480 --> 32:32.360
Any objections?

32:32.360 --> 32:34.570
Of course, no.

32:34.950 --> 32:36.360
The only thing left is...

32:37.110 --> 32:39.320
Tomioka.

32:45.120 --> 32:49.290
I just got back from a mission,
and now I have to take the training.

32:49.290 --> 32:50.630
I can't stand it.

32:50.630 --> 32:52.920
Are you going now?

32:52.920 --> 32:57.760
Yeah, right. We have to take
the Hashira Training in turns.

32:57.760 --> 33:00.300
Huh? Really? Isn't that great?

33:00.680 --> 33:04.140
It's not great at all. Horrible.
It's hell.

33:04.140 --> 33:06.890
Whoever proposed this
should die already.

33:06.890 --> 33:07.730
Hey!

33:07.730 --> 33:12.980
Sparring with superiors
is a shortcut to improving.

33:13.320 --> 33:18.700
When you face someone stronger,
you absorb it and get stronger yourself.

33:24.740 --> 33:29.330
If you're being so optimistic,
then we're no longer friends from today!

33:29.330 --> 33:30.750
Ouch! Ouch! It hurts!

33:30.750 --> 33:33.380
It's okay for you!
Your bone fracture hasn't healed yet!

33:33.380 --> 33:35.260
You can just go back to sleep
and get warm!

33:35.260 --> 33:37.420
For me? I have to go to train now!

33:37.420 --> 33:39.720
Do you know how I feel?!

33:41.010 --> 33:42.760
I'm sorry!

33:44.930 --> 33:45.850
Zenitsu.

33:45.850 --> 33:47.810
Don't talk to me!

33:47.810 --> 33:49.390
Wait a minute.

33:49.390 --> 33:52.860
I forgot to say thank you.

33:55.190 --> 34:00.070
When I was fighting Upper Rank Four
and almost couldn't move one of my legs,

34:00.070 --> 34:04.330
Thanks to the Thunder Breathing
trick you taught me,

34:04.330 --> 34:06.330
I was able to cut the demon's head.

34:08.000 --> 34:11.830
Of course,
I couldn't do it as fast as you.

34:11.830 --> 34:13.420
Thank you so much.

34:14.000 --> 34:18.870
Sometimes connections with others
can help us get through tight spots.

34:18.870 --> 34:25.390
I'm sure that everything we learn in the
Hashira Training will lead to a better future.

34:30.270 --> 34:35.140
You fool! Don't think
that's going to fix my mood!

34:35.140 --> 34:37.980
Oh, he looks happy. That's good.

34:37.980 --> 34:40.890
See you later, Tanjiro. Get well soon.

34:40.890 --> 34:44.990
Oh jeez, everyone's really helpless
without me.

34:49.830 --> 34:52.790
I'm really thankful, Zenitsu.

34:57.000 --> 34:59.510
So slow! So slow! So slow!
You're all slow!

35:03.220 --> 35:07.390
What the hell are you doing?
You guys are really unbelievable!

35:09.180 --> 35:11.890
First of all,
your basic fitness is non-existent!

35:11.890 --> 35:13.900
This is just simply running!

35:13.900 --> 35:17.690
Faster! Move as if the demons
are chasing you!

35:19.030 --> 35:21.530
Hey, hey, I can't hear your voices!

35:21.530 --> 35:23.150
No need to lick the ground!

35:23.150 --> 35:25.120
Now isn't break time yet!

35:25.120 --> 35:27.330
Run one more lap!

35:27.330 --> 35:28.700
Please, no more.

35:28.700 --> 35:30.250
You guys are total losers.

35:30.250 --> 35:34.040
The training of the active Hashiras
after this will be even harder.

35:34.750 --> 35:38.840
As I expected, Sir Tengen is
more lively when he's on duty.

35:38.840 --> 35:42.550
Well, of course.
And we must do our best to help him.

35:42.550 --> 35:47.260
Since everyone's hungry,
let's make lots, lots of onigiris!

35:47.260 --> 35:48.510
Yeah.

35:57.940 --> 36:01.570
Sir Tengen, lunch is ready!

36:01.900 --> 36:02.900
Thanks!

36:02.900 --> 36:06.070
Hey! Your meals are ready!

36:06.070 --> 36:07.780
I can't.

36:07.780 --> 36:09.870
I don't feel like eating.

36:11.370 --> 36:13.620
You guys are sloppy, really.

36:13.620 --> 36:17.290
Sir Tengen.
Please, don't be so mad at them.

36:17.290 --> 36:22.170
I'd love to, but if I send them to
the next Hashira like this,

36:22.170 --> 36:24.220
I'll be the one to blame.

36:24.220 --> 36:25.720
Here, Sir Tengen.

36:25.720 --> 36:26.300
Thanks.

36:26.300 --> 36:28.720
It's miso soup with lots of salt.

36:31.850 --> 36:35.600
This is nothing to their training.
Believe me.

36:36.730 --> 36:40.690
You're in charge of
basic fitness workouts, correct?

36:40.690 --> 36:43.610
What kind of training do they take
after this?

36:43.610 --> 36:45.490
After my training...

36:45.490 --> 36:48.620
First, Tokito's high-speed
movement training.

36:48.620 --> 36:52.620
He'd do harsh things,
even with his poker face.

36:52.620 --> 36:56.580
Next, you'll be greeted by
Kanroji's hellish flexibility training.

36:56.580 --> 37:00.290
Next comes Iguro's training.
Improving swordsmanship.

37:00.290 --> 37:02.500
I tell you,
the Serpent Hashira is stubborn.

37:02.500 --> 37:04.420
Next, Shinazugawa's training.

37:04.420 --> 37:06.880
I heard it's endless striking training,

37:06.880 --> 37:09.640
but I'm sure as the name implies,
it'll be no end.

37:09.640 --> 37:13.180
The last one is Himejima's
muscle strengthening.

37:13.180 --> 37:15.980
You have to throw away
your humanity for this one.

37:15.980 --> 37:17.730
The Hashiras are also expected to

37:17.730 --> 37:25.320
improve their strength as they have to deal
with the Corps members, one after another.

37:25.320 --> 37:27.530
Isn't that flamboyant?

37:28.410 --> 37:32.080
I wish I had the chance to train
with everything I got as well.

37:33.240 --> 37:35.580
I'll leave it to you, everyone.

37:41.420 --> 37:45.420
This ain't gonna raise my temperature.

37:45.420 --> 37:46.800
You guys are too weak!

37:49.050 --> 37:51.890
Good, keep it up.

37:51.890 --> 37:54.100
Try it a bit wider!

37:55.970 --> 37:59.350
You never know where
the enemy will attack.

38:01.940 --> 38:03.060
Feel it!

38:04.820 --> 38:09.610
With all these openings, you would have
been eaten by demons three times.

38:09.990 --> 38:13.320
In order to maintain mark condition...

38:13.320 --> 38:15.450
Your side is open.

38:19.330 --> 38:21.830
Do your best, everyone.

38:22.460 --> 38:25.500
We're doing this to slay all the demons.

38:25.500 --> 38:28.840
For the Master's sake.

38:28.840 --> 38:32.590
For the Corps members who
have died so far.

38:32.590 --> 38:35.970
For the people who are still alive.

38:36.390 --> 38:39.680
We have to get through this.

38:39.680 --> 38:41.520
Hang in there.

38:49.780 --> 38:51.400
What's the matter?

38:57.660 --> 38:58.660
I'm bleeding!

38:59.120 --> 39:01.500
What are you doing so suddenly?
That's mean!

39:03.790 --> 39:05.500
Hurry, hurry.

39:05.500 --> 39:09.210
It's a letter from the Master.
Read it at once.

39:09.210 --> 39:11.800
A letter for me?

39:11.800 --> 39:14.180
I wonder what it is.

39:17.640 --> 39:22.140
Tomioka doesn't participate
in the Hashira Training?

39:38.580 --> 39:40.330
Master Kagaya,

39:40.330 --> 39:48.040
the Hashiras have begun to train
the Corps members for the upcoming battle.

39:49.340 --> 39:57.220
Your children are carrying your will
and connecting with your feelings.

39:58.510 --> 40:03.940
They are willing to do it for the long-held
ambition of defeating Muzan Kibutsuji.

40:10.150 --> 40:11.530
Amane.

40:13.490 --> 40:14.570
Yes?

40:17.070 --> 40:23.040
Thank you so much for everything
you have done.

40:32.550 --> 40:33.670
It's my pleasure.

41:19.640 --> 41:21.970
Good evening, Tamayo.

41:28.560 --> 41:33.190
It is dangerous to leave
a window open at night.

41:37.570 --> 41:41.280
But still, the moon is beautiful tonight.

41:42.200 --> 41:43.910
It is a pleasure to meet you.

41:43.910 --> 41:48.410
I am the messenger of Kagaya Ubuyashiki.

41:49.960 --> 41:54.340
I admit. You are very good at hiding.

41:54.340 --> 41:59.720
While I was trying to find you,
Ubuyashiki can no longer move.

42:00.430 --> 42:04.180
How did you find this place?

42:04.970 --> 42:07.640
The human network.

42:07.640 --> 42:12.400
I have identified the previous owner of
this house you bought.

42:12.400 --> 42:18.400
And during the day,
I grasp how Yushiro's vision works.

42:18.990 --> 42:24.240
Even though I am trained,
I am just a crow.

42:24.240 --> 42:27.870
No one is wary of me to begin with.

42:27.870 --> 42:33.250
I have no intention of harming you two,
so rest assured.

42:34.130 --> 42:38.010
Then, what do you want?

42:39.670 --> 42:43.970
You are suspicious of me.
It is understandable.

42:43.970 --> 42:51.600
As expected, it is difficult for me
to gain your trust as Tanjiro did.

42:52.100 --> 42:54.560
What are his intentions?

42:54.560 --> 42:58.860
Is Ubuyashiki trying to deceive me?

43:00.150 --> 43:01.740
Where is Yushiro?

43:01.740 --> 43:04.990
There is no need to worry about Yushiro.

43:05.950 --> 43:09.790
Listen, you can hear
his footsteps running.

43:11.330 --> 43:12.540
Now...

43:13.250 --> 43:15.750
I shall tell you my business.

43:17.670 --> 43:19.340
In the Demon Slayer Corps,

43:19.340 --> 43:24.590
there is also a kid who is knowledgeable
about demon body and pharmacology.

43:24.590 --> 43:29.770
We would like you to look into Nezuko's
transformation together with her.

43:31.980 --> 43:36.230
In order to defeat Muzan Kibutsuji,
would you work with us?

43:37.770 --> 43:40.780
We invite you to the Ubuyashiki residence.

43:41.740 --> 43:47.240
I, a demon, am invited to the
Demon Slayer Corps headquarters?

43:50.080 --> 43:53.080
(Episode 1
In Order to Defeat Muzan Kibutsuji)

43:53.080 --> 43:57.040
To you who is ignorant of
what eternity means

43:57.040 --> 44:00.340
It's time to show you the answer

44:00.340 --> 44:06.640
Beyond the endless spiral

44:22.440 --> 44:25.950
The reason why it sounded like an excuse

44:25.950 --> 44:29.490
A weakness that draws in a fleeting future

44:29.490 --> 44:34.620
You mistake it for strength

44:36.000 --> 44:37.920
So detestable, so detestable

44:37.920 --> 44:39.630
So disgraceful, so disgraceful

44:39.630 --> 44:43.050
The heart that is so bleak

44:43.050 --> 44:44.920
So dark, so dark

44:44.920 --> 44:46.880
That it almost hides the moon

44:46.880 --> 44:50.470
If only you weren't here

44:50.470 --> 44:54.060
It sways and sways

44:54.060 --> 44:57.690
Carrying on its intentions
just like a flower

44:57.690 --> 45:01.070
Taking it all away, taking it all away

45:01.070 --> 45:04.570
It tears the heart just like a storm would

45:04.570 --> 45:08.160
To you who is ignorant of
what eternity means

45:08.160 --> 45:11.700
It's time to show you the answer

45:11.700 --> 45:17.080
Beyond the endless spiral

45:17.080 --> 45:21.210
Who awaits there

47:57.700 --> 47:59.700
For every Hashira Training Arc episode,

47:59.700 --> 48:04.000
I'd like to present every Hashira's
Taisho period secret.

48:04.620 --> 48:05.830
Inosuke!

48:07.040 --> 48:09.920
Can you explain what happened
with these broken glasses?

48:09.920 --> 48:11.300
But you know...

48:11.300 --> 48:12.300
Naughty!

48:13.420 --> 48:17.510
Always being positive is
a good part of you,

48:17.510 --> 48:20.060
but there are some things
you shouldn't do.

48:20.060 --> 48:22.270
Let me see your arm.

48:22.270 --> 48:24.100
I'll treat your wound.

48:24.690 --> 48:27.350
Don't ever do that again, understand?

48:31.110 --> 48:36.820
Shinobu is sure strict,
but she's a very considerate person.

48:36.820 --> 48:38.820
Even at the last Hashira meeting...

48:38.820 --> 48:41.160
Oh my oh my oh my...

48:41.160 --> 48:42.450
Kanroji.

48:43.330 --> 48:44.710
Thank you!

48:44.710 --> 48:46.500
You're welcome.

48:47.040 --> 48:50.250
That's all for this Taisho period secret.

48:50.250 --> 48:51.920
Next up on Episode 2:

48:51.920 --> 48:54.590
"The Sorrows of the Water Hashira,
Giyu Tomioka"

48:54.590 --> 48:55.160
(To be continued)
